    <div class="text">
      <p>
        My Final Year project involved the design and prototyping and analysis
        of an underwater “Nano” glider. Current gliders used in oceanography are
        generally large in scale, often surpassing 50kg in weight. However, for
        Limnological explorations, these large devices are impractical due to
        their lack of manoeuvrability in smaller environments. For this reason,
        the downscaling of underwater gliders is increasing in demand for a
        range of applications.
      </p>
      <div class="frames">
        <img class="mySlides center" src="img/workflow.png" />
        <img class="mySlides center" src="img/concept.PNG" />
        <img class="mySlides center" src="img/Glider profile.png" />
        <img class="mySlides center" src="img/Buoyancy states.png" />
        <button class="w3-btn left" onclick="plusDivs(-1)">&#10094;</button>
