      </div>
      <p>
        The concept selected contains a reservoir connected to a miniature
        motor- pump. Water is ingested and expelled from the system through the
        reservoir to vary the system buoyancy. With hydrofoils attached to the
        hull the glider follows a saw-tooth profile through the water. The
        design was modelled in CAD and refined and iterated by assessing the
        forces and moments in bouyancy calculations document.
      </p>
      <div class="frames">
        <img class="mySlides2 center" src="img/gliderassembly.png" />
